HEADWORD: Exocœtus
<hw>Ex`oc⟦oe⟧"tus</hw></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>exocetus</ets>, L. <ets>exocoetus</ets> a fish that sleeps on the
shore, Gr. <grk>'exw`koitos</grk>, lit., sleeping out; <grk>'e`xw</grk>
outside of + <grk>koi`th</grk> bed.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>A
genus of fishes, including the common flying fishes. See <er>Flying
fish</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

